-- Lufthansa Expects Decline in Operating Profit, CEO Tells NZZ
-- B y   K l a u s   W i l l e
-- 2012-03-24T11:24:35Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-24/lufthansa-expects-decline-in-operating-profit-ceo-tells-nzz.html
Deutsche Lufthansa AG (LHA) ’s operating
profit for 2012 will be in the “middle three-digit million euro
area,” less than what it made in the previous year, the
airline’s chief executive officer, Christoph Franz, told  Neue
Zuercher Zeitung  in an  interview .  Lufthansa on March 7 reported an operating profit of 820
million euros ($1.1 billion) for 2011.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Klaus Wille in Zurich at 
